## Conclusion

A machine learning-based support ticket classification system was successfully developed using Natural Language Processing techniques and the Linear Support Vector Classifier (LinearSVC).

The model was trained on 47,837 support tickets across eight categories and achieved an accuracy of **85.6%**. Results indicate that the system can effectively classify support requests and assist organizations in automating ticket routing processes.

This project demonstrates the practical application of machine learning in business operations and customer support environments, providing measurable improvements in efficiency and scalability.

